<plot>Saverio and his seven-year-old brother Augusto have been living with Uncle Fausto and Aunt Domenica since their parents died in a tragic car accident four years previously. Saverio has a strong spiritual bond with nature and is planning to spend part of his summer break in the high pastures to experience life as a shepherd and to learn how to make 'Bitto cheese'. However, one day whilst exploring the meadows by the river in the company of Augusto and his best friend Charlie (the nanny goat), Saverio falls and fractures his leg. Although disappointed that he has to put his plan on hold. his summer still turns out to be the most memorable of his childhood when he finds his first 'porcino' - the highly esteemed 'Boletus Edulis'. The unexpected arrival of Valentino, from the USA, after a forty-year absence gives the village gossips something to talk about and Saverio's adventures continue as the gentle community is thrust into turmoil when a baby mysteriously disappears.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?258263</url></doc>
